INTRODUCTION: Colorectal cancer (CRC) is one of the main causes of 
cancer-related morbidity and mortality worldwide. Mortality is most often 
attributable to metastatic disease. Despite the progress achieved so far, life 
expectancy continues to be limited in most patients. Ramucirumab, a most recent 
antiangiogenic drug, is vying in the race to metastatic CRC (mCRC) treatment 
